	intensive and are not currently available in all standard statistical
	software. We describe an alternative approach using Poisson based
	Generalised Linear Models (GLMs).We illustrate, through application
	and simulation, the Poisson approach both classically and in a Bayesian
	framework, in two-stage and one-stage approaches. We outline the
	benefits of our one-stage approach through extension to modelling
	treatment-covariate interactions and non-proportional hazards. Ten
	trials of hypertension treatment, with all-cause death the outcome
	of interest, are used to apply and assess the approach.We show that
