  number      = {2},
  pages       = {148--152},
  volume      = {36},
  abstract    = {Background: Relative survival is an extensively used method in population
	based cancer studies as it provides a measure of survival without
	the need for accurate cause of death information. It gives an estimate
	for the probability of dying from cancer in the absence of other
	causes by estimating the excess mortality in the study population
