	METHODS: Glasziou and Irwig have outlined the concept of net clinical
	treatment benefit for identifying the patients for whom the potential
	benefits of treatment outweigh the possible side effects. This study
	revisits the decision whether to use warfarin to treat atrial fibrillation.
	In this analysis, RCT and various sorts of observational data are
