  volume    = {14},
  abstract  = {Comparisons between self-report and clinical psychiatric measures
	have revealed considerable disagreement. It is unsafe to consider
	these measures as directly equivalent, so it would be valuable to
	have a reliable recalibration of one measure in terms of the other.
	We evaluated multiple imputation incorporating a Bayesian approach,
	and a fully Bayesian method, to recalibrate diagnoses from a self-report
	survey interview in terms of those from a clinical interview with
	data from a two-phase national household survey for a practical application,
